{% if api_style == "api-platform" %}
## API Platform

API Platform is the primary API layer. Key concepts:

### Resources

API resources are PHP classes annotated with `#[ApiResource]`:

```php
#[ApiResource(
    operations: [
        new GetCollection(),
        new Get(),
        new Post(processor: CreateUserProcessor::class),
        new Put(processor: UpdateUserProcessor::class),
        new Delete(),
    ],
    normalizationContext: ['groups' => ['user:read']],
    denormalizationContext: ['groups' => ['user:write']],
)]
class User { ... }
```

### Serialization Groups

Use Symfony Serializer groups consistently:

| Group | Usage |
|-------|-------|
| `{resource}:read` | Exposed on GET responses |
| `{resource}:write` | Accepted on POST/PUT/PATCH |
| `{resource}:list` | Subset for collection responses |
| `{resource}:admin` | Fields visible only to admins |

### State Providers and Processors

For custom data sources or write logic, use providers and processors instead of overriding controllers:

- `StateProviderInterface` - custom read logic (replaces `CollectionDataProvider`)
- `StateProcessorInterface` - custom write logic (replaces `DataPersister`)

Never put business logic in providers/processors. They should call a service.

### Filters and Pagination

```php
#[ApiFilter(SearchFilter::class, properties: ['email' => 'exact', 'name' => 'partial'])]
#[ApiFilter(OrderFilter::class, properties: ['createdAt', 'name'])]
#[ApiFilter(DateFilter::class, properties: ['createdAt'])]
```

Pagination is enabled by default. Configure via `config/packages/api_platform.yaml`:

```yaml
api_platform:
    defaults:
        pagination_items_per_page: 25
        pagination_maximum_items_per_page: 100
        pagination_client_items_per_page: true
```

{% elif api_style == "custom-controllers" %}
## Custom Controllers

All endpoints are implemented as Symfony controllers using PHP attribute routing.

### Controller Conventions

```php
#[Route('/api/v1/users', name: 'api_users_')]
final class UserController extends AbstractController
{
    public function __construct(
        private readonly UserService $userService,
        private readonly SerializerInterface $serializer,
    ) {}

    #[Route('', name: 'list', methods: ['GET'])]
    public function list(Request $request): JsonResponse
    {
        $users = $this->userService->list($request->query->getInt('page', 1));
        return $this->json($users, context: ['groups' => ['user:read']]);
    }
}
```

### Response Shape

All API responses use a consistent envelope. See [API Conventions](api-conventions.md).

{% elif api_style == "fos-rest" %}
## FOSRestBundle

FOSRestBundle provides view handling, format negotiation, and exception handling.

### Controller Conventions

```php
#[Route('/api/v1')]
final class UserController extends AbstractFOSRestController
{
    #[Rest\Get('/users', name: 'api_users_list')]
    #[View(serializerGroups: ['user:read'])]
    public function list(): QueryBuilder|array
    {
        return $this->userService->findAll();
    }
}
```

### Format Negotiation

Configure accepted formats in `config/packages/fos_rest.yaml`. Enforce JSON-only for API routes.

