## Database Schema Conventions

- All tables use **snake_case** names derived from the entity class name (Doctrine default)
- Primary keys are `id` columns of type `uuid` (preferred) or `bigint`
- Every table has `created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL` and `updated_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL`
- Foreign key columns are named `{entity}_id` (e.g., `user_id`)
- Boolean columns are named with the `is_` or `has_` prefix
- Nullable columns are only used when `NULL` has a distinct semantic meaning

### Migration Rules

- **Always** generate migrations with `php bin/console make:migration`
- **Never** edit a migration after it has been applied to any environment
- **Never** write raw SQL in application code; use Doctrine entities and migrations
- Migration files are committed and tracked in version control
- Each migration has a descriptive docblock comment

