{% if use_rabbitmq %}
## Async Messaging (RabbitMQ)

Symfony Messenger with the AMQP transport handles async workloads.

### Transport Configuration

```yaml
# config/packages/messenger.yaml
framework:
    messenger:
        transports:
            async:
                dsn: '%env(MESSENGER_TRANSPORT_DSN)%'
                retry_strategy:
                    max_retries: 3
                    delay: 1000
                    multiplier: 2
            failed: 'doctrine://default?queue_name=failed'

        routing:
            App\Message\SendEmailMessage: async
            App\Message\ProcessImportMessage: async
```

### Message Pattern

```php
// Message (plain object)
final readonly class SendEmailMessage
{
    public function __construct(
        public string $recipient,
        public string $subject,
        public string $template,
    ) {}
}

// Handler
#[AsMessageHandler]
final class SendEmailMessageHandler
{
    public function __invoke(SendEmailMessage $message): void
    {
        // send the email
    }
}
```

### Running Workers

```bash
# Consume indefinitely (use Supervisor in production)
php bin/console messenger:consume async --limit=100 --memory-limit=128M

# Inspect the failed queue
php bin/console messenger:failed:show

# Retry a failed message
php bin/console messenger:failed:retry
```

{% endif %}

{% if use_redis %}
## Caching (Redis)

Redis is configured as a Symfony Cache adapter.

### Cache Pools

```yaml
# config/packages/cache.yaml
framework:
    cache:
        app: cache.adapter.redis
        default_redis_provider: '%env(REDIS_URL)%'
        pools:
            cache.app:
                adapter: cache.adapter.redis
            cache.api_responses:
                adapter: cache.adapter.redis
                default_lifetime: 300
```

### Usage in Services

```php
public function __construct(
    #[Autowire(service: 'cache.api_responses')]
    private readonly CacheInterface $cache,
) {}

public function getExpensiveData(string $key): array
{
    return $this->cache->get($key, function (ItemInterface $item): array {
        $item->expiresAfter(300);
        return $this->doExpensiveQuery();
    });
}
```

### Cache Invalidation

Use cache tags for grouped invalidation:

```php
$item->tag(['user_' . $userId, 'users']);
$this->cache->invalidateTags(['user_' . $userId]);
```

