## Testing Architecture

Strategy: **{{ test_strategy }}**

### Test Directory Structure

```
tests/
├── Unit/                    # Pure unit tests - no database, no HTTP, no framework
│   ├── Service/
│   ├── Entity/
{% if use_ddd %}
│   ├── Domain/
│   └── Application/
{% else %}
│   └── Repository/          # Repository method tests with an in-memory implementation
{% endif %}
├── Integration/             # Tests against a real database (test schema)
│   ├── Repository/
│   └── Service/
└── Functional/              # Full HTTP request/response tests via Symfony's test client
    └── Api/
```

### Unit Tests

- Test one class in isolation
- Mock all collaborators with `createMock()` or Prophecy
- No `setUp` database fixtures
- Fast: entire suite runs in under 5 seconds

### Integration Tests

- Use a separate test database (`DATABASE_URL` in `.env.test`)
- Load fixtures with `doctrine/data-fixtures` or `zenstruck/foundry`
- Reset the database between tests using transactions (rollback after each test)
- Test the full stack through the service layer

### Functional Tests

- Use `Symfony\Bundle\FrameworkBundle\Test\WebTestCase`
- Make HTTP requests via `$client->request('GET', '/api/v1/users')`
- Assert HTTP status codes, response structure, and headers
- Use fixtures for predictable test data

{% if test_strategy == "phpunit-and-behat" %}
### Behat (BDD)

Behat scenarios describe API behavior in business language:

```gherkin
Feature: User management
  Scenario: Create a new user
    Given I am authenticated as an admin
    When I send a POST request to "/api/v1/users" with:
      | email | test@example.com |
      | name  | Test User        |
    Then the response status code should be 201
    And the response should contain "test@example.com"
```

Feature files live in `features/`. Step definitions live in `features/bootstrap/`.

{% elif test_strategy == "pest" %}
### Pest

Tests use Pest's expressive syntax:

```php
it('returns a user by id', function () {
    $user = UserFactory::createOne();
    $response = $this->getJson('/api/v1/users/' . $user->getId());
    $response->assertStatus(200)->assertJsonFragment(['email' => $user->getEmail()]);
});
```

{% endif %}

